WEBVTT

00:06.484 --> 00:06.702
.

00:06.745 --> 00:09.052
- Previously on "Shooter"...
- Run along, sweetheart.

00:09.096 --> 00:11.011
[gunshot]
Ah! [groaning]

00:11.054 --> 00:13.056
- Bo's filing charges
against you.

00:13.100 --> 00:14.318
Might wanna call a lawyer.

00:14.362 --> 00:15.493
- I'll settle for
a clue of who you are

00:15.537 --> 00:16.929
and what the hell
am I doing here?

00:16.973 --> 00:18.496
- Patricia Gregson,

00:18.540 --> 00:21.108
Deputy Director
Defense Intelligence Agency.

00:21.151 --> 00:23.023
- Well, I'm glad I can still
count on you, Patricia.

00:23.066 --> 00:26.504
- Don't let your problems
become my problems again.

00:26.548 --> 00:28.245
- This isn't a suicide,
and it's not some coincidence.

00:28.289 --> 00:29.855
Your boss did this.

00:29.899 --> 00:31.335
Help me take Hayes down.

00:31.379 --> 00:33.120
- Okay, what do you need?

00:33.163 --> 00:36.340
- The official report says your
father was alone when he died.

00:36.384 --> 00:38.864
You and I both know
that was not the case.

00:38.908 --> 00:40.040
[gunshot]

00:40.083 --> 00:42.520
- You might wanna sit down.

00:42.564 --> 00:44.218
[glass shatters]

00:44.261 --> 00:46.698
- We saw the news,
but I'll still need the card.

00:46.742 --> 00:49.049
- I resigned from the FBI
this morning.

00:49.092 --> 00:51.268
Time to start my new job.

00:52.313 --> 00:55.707
[soft, atmospheric music]

00:55.751 --> 00:57.709
male news reporter:
...and 72 in Deming.

00:57.753 --> 00:59.885
We'll be seeing some cooler
temperatures in the evening,

00:59.929 --> 01:01.713
with lows of 58 in El Paso,

01:01.757 --> 01:04.716
56 in Alamogordo,
and 60 in Deming.

01:04.760 --> 01:06.718
Traffic through downtown
has slowed a little bit

01:06.762 --> 01:08.285
on the northbound side,

01:08.329 --> 01:09.852
with a fender bender
on the right shoulder.

01:09.895 --> 01:11.636
You wanna watch out
for that to be sure.

01:11.680 --> 01:13.812
Should be cleared up
shortly though we hope.

01:13.856 --> 01:15.249
I-10, lookout--

01:15.292 --> 01:22.560
♪

01:30.568 --> 01:32.092
- [yelling]

01:33.789 --> 01:36.966
[groaning]

01:37.009 --> 01:38.968
[birds chirping]

01:39.011 --> 01:46.236
♪

01:48.020 --> 01:49.283
[arm snaps]
- Ahh!

01:49.326 --> 01:52.938
[desolate music]

01:52.982 --> 01:56.942
- Do you think Isaac Johnson
recruited you by accident?

01:56.986 --> 01:59.293
Atlas and the Swaggers

01:59.336 --> 02:01.773
have been interlinked
since the beginning.

02:01.817 --> 02:04.820
How much do you think
you know about your father?

02:04.863 --> 02:07.431
♪

02:07.475 --> 02:11.174
- Good morning, Bob Lee.
- Thanks, Anne.

02:11.218 --> 02:13.176
I'm so happy
you could stay with us.

02:13.220 --> 02:15.178
- Aw, you're doing me
the favor.

02:15.222 --> 02:17.137
- You know, Anne might
look at property down here.

02:17.180 --> 02:19.487
- Really?
- Maybe.

02:19.530 --> 02:22.838
I miss my mister,
and I miss my Mary.

02:22.881 --> 02:25.884
[laughter]
- Aww!

02:27.886 --> 02:30.541
- What's up?

02:30.585 --> 02:33.849
- Uh, I'm just...
Working something over,

02:33.892 --> 02:35.503
something about my dad.

02:37.244 --> 02:41.465
- Mary, why don't we go finish
your daddy's picture in my room

02:41.509 --> 02:43.511
and you can help me
finish unpacking?

02:43.554 --> 02:44.903
- Okay.

02:47.993 --> 02:49.473
- So, what's going on?

02:49.517 --> 02:52.172
- Solotov knew some things
about my dad's death.

02:52.215 --> 02:55.218
I just--
I just can't shake it.

02:55.262 --> 02:58.395
- Yeah, well, I'm sure
that he researched it.

02:58.439 --> 02:59.788
He was a pretty good liar,
you know?

02:59.831 --> 03:03.748
- No, baby...
he knew that I was there.

03:03.792 --> 03:05.533
Nobody knew that.

03:05.576 --> 03:07.839
Wasn't in any of the reports.

03:10.929 --> 03:13.497
- Honey, you've only been home
for a few days.

03:13.541 --> 03:16.500
I'd like you to stay around
for a few more, you know,

03:16.544 --> 03:19.155
spend some time with Mary.

03:19.199 --> 03:22.202
And no offense, but your dad's
been gone for over 30 years.

03:22.245 --> 03:24.334
I mean, it can wait
a few days, right?

03:24.378 --> 03:27.468
- Yeah, yeah, I just--
I got a couple questions

03:27.511 --> 03:30.514
about Jimmy Poole's escape
from the prison,

03:30.558 --> 03:33.996
and then that'll probably be
the end of it.

03:34.039 --> 03:36.868
- Okay.

03:36.912 --> 03:38.957
Don't spend all day, okay?

03:41.090 --> 03:44.049
[foreboding music]

03:44.093 --> 03:51.274
♪

03:59.587 --> 04:01.806
- Where is everyone?

04:01.850 --> 04:05.027
- ICE used this as a holding
facility since 9/11, sir.

04:05.070 --> 04:08.335
It's being converted into
a women's prison.

04:08.378 --> 04:11.686
♪

04:11.729 --> 04:13.165
- [chuckles]

04:13.209 --> 04:16.908
I haven't heard the name
Jimmy Poole in a long time.

04:16.952 --> 04:19.302
Real piece of shit.

04:19.346 --> 04:21.391
He got what was coming to him.

04:21.435 --> 04:23.959
- I was curious
about his escape.

04:24.002 --> 04:25.395
You remember any of it?

04:25.439 --> 04:27.092
- Eh, it was nothing
escaping then.

04:27.136 --> 04:30.008
You know, Jimmy sweet-talked
his way into the work farm here

04:30.052 --> 04:31.662
to be closer to his wife.

04:31.706 --> 04:34.839
He was looking to run
from the moment he got here.

04:34.883 --> 04:37.538
- Why'd he wait until that day?
- He was a criminal.

04:37.581 --> 04:39.844
They don't tend to operate
with a plan.

04:41.629 --> 04:43.935
- Were you on duty?
- Yep.

04:43.979 --> 04:45.676
Highway cleanup.

04:45.720 --> 04:48.853
Jimmy asked to use the head
and never came back.

04:50.202 --> 04:51.334
- Huh.

04:51.378 --> 04:54.337
[solemn bass music]

04:54.381 --> 04:58.254
♪

04:58.298 --> 05:00.909
- Something wrong?

05:00.952 --> 05:03.651
- I just heard
he ran from here,

05:03.694 --> 05:06.567
but hell,
it was 30 years ago.

05:06.610 --> 05:09.134
- Yeah, maybe he did.

05:09.178 --> 05:11.049
Like you said...

05:11.093 --> 05:13.356
it was a long time in the past.

05:13.400 --> 05:15.663
♪

05:15.706 --> 05:18.796
- Bama Cattle.
I saw their boxes inside.

05:18.840 --> 05:21.582
Guess that's where you get
all your provisions, huh?

05:21.625 --> 05:23.627
Convenient having 'em so close.

05:23.671 --> 05:27.718
I heard a story they were
hiring undocumented labor.

05:27.762 --> 05:31.069
Cut some kinda sweetheart deal
with the feds.

05:31.113 --> 05:33.376
Must be nice.

05:33.420 --> 05:36.031
- I wouldn't know
nothing about that.

05:36.074 --> 05:38.729
♪

05:38.773 --> 05:42.167
Well, it's time
to get back to it.

05:42.211 --> 05:43.995
- Thank you for your time.

05:44.039 --> 05:49.914
♪

05:49.958 --> 05:52.917
[phone ringing]

05:52.961 --> 05:54.354
- Bama Cattle?

05:54.397 --> 05:55.572
[knocking]

05:55.616 --> 05:57.618
- What is it?
I'm busy.

05:57.661 --> 05:59.881
- Hm, we got a problem.

05:59.924 --> 06:03.580
Bob Lee Swagger just paid
a visit to Wilson Penitentiary.

06:03.624 --> 06:07.584
He's asking a whole lot
of questions.

06:07.628 --> 06:09.499
- Son of a bitch.

06:09.543 --> 06:12.720
[tense music]

06:12.763 --> 06:14.243
[sighs]

06:14.286 --> 06:17.246
[dramatic music]

06:17.289 --> 06:24.514
♪

06:26.473 --> 06:26.690
.

06:26.734 --> 06:29.519
[tense music]

06:29.563 --> 06:32.261
♪

06:32.304 --> 06:35.003
- Did we have
a meeting scheduled?

06:35.046 --> 06:38.049
I'd let you make me coffee,
but I take mine without poison.

06:38.093 --> 06:40.095
- We're not stopping
until Atlas is finished.

06:40.138 --> 06:42.314
- I heard you were finished,
Agent Memphis,

06:42.358 --> 06:45.056
or...I guess
it's just Nadine now?

06:45.100 --> 06:46.797
- Yeah, well, I got tired of
trying to figure out

06:46.841 --> 06:48.408
who the good guys were.

06:48.451 --> 06:50.235
Plus, I recently
came into some money,

06:50.279 --> 06:53.282
figured I'd open my own shop,
like you.

06:53.325 --> 06:54.805
- Ah...

06:54.849 --> 06:56.720
You kept the Atlas money.

06:56.764 --> 06:58.548
I'm glad you did.

06:58.592 --> 07:00.463
There's a lot of competition
out there, Nadine.

07:00.507 --> 07:03.248
Private intelligence needs
more than just muscle,

07:03.292 --> 07:05.425
Sometimes you need to
show some restraint.

07:05.468 --> 07:07.427
- Atlas has a lot
of loose ends.

07:07.470 --> 07:10.778
We'd like to tie them out.
- Around their necks, no doubt.

07:10.821 --> 07:13.476
- Whatever works.

07:13.520 --> 07:17.219
- So why come to me?

07:17.262 --> 07:20.396
- 'Cause you know everyone
and everything in this town.

07:20.440 --> 07:22.833
J. Edgar would've been
jealous of your black book.

07:22.877 --> 07:24.182
- [chuckles]

07:24.226 --> 07:27.490
And, uh...
what do I get out of this?

07:27.534 --> 07:29.057
- Nature hates a vacuum.

07:29.100 --> 07:30.580
Point us in
the right direction,

07:30.624 --> 07:31.973
and we'll handle the rest.

07:32.016 --> 07:34.279
- You think Hayes was
the end of the line?

07:34.323 --> 07:38.109
Atlas isn't done,
far from it.

07:38.153 --> 07:39.894
- How big is it?

07:39.937 --> 07:41.199
- Maybe you should've
asked Hayes

07:41.243 --> 07:44.376
before he had
his heart attack.

07:46.683 --> 07:50.339
- Burial by paperwork.

07:50.382 --> 07:52.472
Ah.

07:52.515 --> 07:55.387
Bo Winnick wants to extort you
over his ringing ear,

07:55.431 --> 07:57.302
he's going to have
to pay for it.

07:57.346 --> 07:59.740
Sign there, initial there.

08:02.307 --> 08:04.527
Uh, I have a system.

08:04.571 --> 08:05.833
- I hope so. [laughs]

08:05.876 --> 08:08.618
- Problem is,
I've forgotten most of it.

08:08.662 --> 08:10.141
- You know what, Sam,
why don't you let me

08:10.185 --> 08:12.317
help you get organized?
No, come on.

08:12.361 --> 08:13.449
Look, you're not taking
a dime from us.

08:13.493 --> 08:15.016
It's the least that I can do.

08:15.059 --> 08:16.931
- Your husband doesn't
need you at home?

08:16.974 --> 08:20.108
- [chuckles]
Sam, contrary to the...

08:20.151 --> 08:24.504
décor of this office,
we are not stuck in the 1950s.

08:24.547 --> 08:27.637
Plus, Bob Lee's already
on another mission.

08:27.681 --> 08:28.986
He, uh--

08:29.030 --> 08:30.161
He thinks that Earl's death

08:30.205 --> 08:33.991
needs to be
reinvestigated, so...

08:34.035 --> 08:35.253
- Earl?

08:35.297 --> 08:37.647
- Yeah, Solotov
got in his head.

08:37.691 --> 08:39.344
I don't know, it seems
a little out there,

08:39.388 --> 08:44.045
but I hope he doesn't
take it too far.

08:44.088 --> 08:46.177
- Well, if it makes
you feel any better,

08:46.221 --> 08:48.571
he won't find much
about Earl's death.

08:48.615 --> 08:51.922
That dark night gave up
all her mysteries:

08:51.966 --> 08:53.663
Two shooters, two dead.

08:53.707 --> 08:55.796
- Well...

08:55.839 --> 08:57.624
you know Bob Lee.

08:57.667 --> 08:59.843
- That I do.

08:59.887 --> 09:02.454
- Hi, uh, two vegetarian,

09:02.498 --> 09:04.195
extra spicy,

09:04.239 --> 09:06.850
and, uh, just a water.

09:06.894 --> 09:08.765
Thank you.
- Thank you.

09:08.809 --> 09:09.853
- Thanks.

09:09.897 --> 09:12.856
[Mariachi music playing]

09:12.900 --> 09:14.771
- Vegetarian.

09:14.815 --> 09:17.165
Of course.

09:17.208 --> 09:18.862
- I don't wanna talk to you.

09:18.906 --> 09:20.734
- Do I look like I'm asking?

09:20.777 --> 09:22.431
Vamos.

09:26.130 --> 09:27.610
- You literally
could've just texted.

09:27.654 --> 09:29.438
- You shouldn't
even be in D.C.

09:29.481 --> 09:31.048
You remember
how we found Denning?

09:31.092 --> 09:32.267
It took us ten seconds
to find you.

09:32.310 --> 09:33.921
How long before Atlas does?

09:33.964 --> 09:35.400
- I'm not worried
about Atlas anymore.

09:35.444 --> 09:37.141
Hayes's heart attack
took care of that. It's over.

09:37.185 --> 09:38.839
- Hayes is not the end of this.

09:38.882 --> 09:41.885
We need access to his safe
before anyone else gets to it.

09:41.929 --> 09:43.713
- No one else knows it's there.

09:43.757 --> 09:47.499
You wanna get in his safe,
run for Senate, win his seat.

09:47.543 --> 09:49.501
Did you actually think I was
gonna help you with this?

09:49.545 --> 09:50.720
- You still have
security clearance.

09:50.764 --> 09:51.982
- No, he fired me.

09:52.026 --> 09:53.549
- He never filed the paperwork.

09:53.593 --> 09:56.204
As far as anyone knows,
you still work for him.

09:58.467 --> 09:59.903
- I'd rather not.

09:59.947 --> 10:01.644
- Well, that's how I felt
about meeting your mother,

10:01.688 --> 10:04.081
but I went anyway.
- Not the same thing.

10:04.125 --> 10:05.779
- I would love
to meet your mother.

10:05.822 --> 10:07.345
Where does she live?

10:07.389 --> 10:09.696
- Excuse me?
- She like roses?

10:09.739 --> 10:14.614
- Harris, consider it
a personal favor...

10:14.657 --> 10:16.224
for me.

10:16.267 --> 10:19.227
[dark music]

10:19.270 --> 10:26.495
♪

10:27.322 --> 10:28.758
- Thanks for meeting me.

10:28.802 --> 10:31.761
- I have to say,
I'm not surprised,

10:31.805 --> 10:34.198
but I'm not happy either.

10:34.242 --> 10:36.461
Last thing in the world
I wanna be doing

10:36.505 --> 10:38.812
is reliving your daddy's death,

10:38.855 --> 10:41.118
but like your daddy,

10:41.162 --> 10:43.207
I can see you're
not gonna listen.

10:43.251 --> 10:45.688
That's the Poole file.

10:48.343 --> 10:50.824
Been closed since '08.

10:53.827 --> 10:55.872
- Was this pretty much
the layout?

10:55.916 --> 10:58.179
- I believe so.

10:58.222 --> 11:00.660
To tell the truth,
I never banked here.

11:00.703 --> 11:07.667
♪

11:07.928 --> 11:10.713
- So 12:38 p.m....

11:10.757 --> 11:12.889
- Everybody get the hell
on the ground!

11:12.933 --> 11:15.500
Don't you move!
Don't you try to draw on me.

11:15.544 --> 11:16.980
Don't you reach for that.

11:17.024 --> 11:18.286
- Hitting it at lunch

11:18.329 --> 11:19.766
was the smartest thing
Jimmy did that day.

11:19.809 --> 11:22.290
Manager was gone,
security detail halved.

11:22.333 --> 11:24.118
- I'll be taking this.

11:24.161 --> 11:26.686
Thank you. Don't you move.

11:26.729 --> 11:29.210
Hey, hands up against the wall!

11:29.253 --> 11:31.908
And fill that up!

11:31.952 --> 11:34.998
- Silent alarm
came in at 12:39.

11:35.042 --> 11:37.392
We got the call and rolled.

11:37.435 --> 11:39.089
Remember when I came
to get your daddy?

11:39.133 --> 11:40.569
- Right now! Hurry up!

11:40.612 --> 11:42.179
And don't you give me
no dye pack, honey,

11:42.223 --> 11:43.659
or I'm gonna come down,
and I'm gonna dot your i's.

11:43.703 --> 11:45.530
You got that?
You understand?

11:45.574 --> 11:47.489
All right, hurry up,
I ain't got all day.

11:47.532 --> 11:50.013
Don't move!
Don't look at me!

11:50.057 --> 11:52.712
Hey, hey, hey, hey,
don't you make another move.

11:52.755 --> 11:55.062
Don't you make another move.
We got ourselves a hero, huh?

11:55.105 --> 11:56.716
Y'all see this?

11:56.759 --> 11:58.195
A real hero, huh?

11:58.239 --> 11:59.719
[tense music]

11:59.762 --> 12:01.982
- Ahh! Ahh!

12:02.025 --> 12:04.245
- Now you got yourself a story.
- [groans]

12:04.288 --> 12:06.551
- Tell your friends.

12:06.595 --> 12:08.989
This for me?
There we go.

12:09.032 --> 12:11.165
Thank you very much.
Y'all have a nice day.

12:11.208 --> 12:13.558
Don't look at me!
Don't move!

12:13.602 --> 12:15.778
- Where'd he get the Colt?
- Don't know.

12:15.822 --> 12:17.606
- It's a nice piece of iron.

12:17.649 --> 12:19.608
Guy breaks out of prison,
and two hours later,

12:19.651 --> 12:22.567
he's got a sports car
and brandishing that thing?

12:22.611 --> 12:24.787
- Car reported stolen
at the dealership.

12:24.831 --> 12:26.571
He could've hit
any house between

12:26.615 --> 12:29.183
the work farm and here
to get the gun.

12:29.226 --> 12:30.575
♪

12:30.619 --> 12:33.143
This isn't a cold case,
Bob Lee.

12:33.187 --> 12:35.972
It's closed.
Earl made sure of that.

12:36.016 --> 12:38.801
♪

12:38.845 --> 12:41.804
This got anything to do with
you being there that night?

12:41.848 --> 12:43.414
- No.

12:43.458 --> 12:47.244
- Listen, Bob Lee, there wasn't
nothing you could've done.

12:47.288 --> 12:48.942
Nothing.

12:48.985 --> 12:50.595
You were just a kid.

12:50.639 --> 12:52.902
[soft ambient music]

12:52.946 --> 12:55.383
And you need to be in the
hospital, at least at home.

12:55.426 --> 12:57.820
- This isn't about me.
It's about my dad.

12:57.864 --> 12:59.691
There's something off
about this whole thing,

12:59.735 --> 13:02.172
and I need to know what it is.

13:02.216 --> 13:04.087
All right, so, what happened
to the security guard?

13:04.131 --> 13:06.176
- I thought I told you to get
down on the floor, old man.

13:06.220 --> 13:07.830
- I got a bad hip, asshole.

13:07.874 --> 13:11.791
You got what you came for.
Now leave.

13:11.834 --> 13:14.794
- I said get down
on the floor now.

13:14.837 --> 13:17.927
- I didn't lie down in Korea,
and I'm not lying down now,

13:17.971 --> 13:20.930
not for the likes of
road trash like you.

13:20.974 --> 13:23.933
[tense music]

13:23.977 --> 13:26.153
♪

13:26.196 --> 13:29.199
- Fair enough.

13:29.243 --> 13:30.287
[gunshot]

13:30.331 --> 13:32.202
[screaming]

13:32.246 --> 13:34.465
You're gonna lie down for me.

13:34.509 --> 13:36.032
And don't move!
What y'all looking at?

13:36.076 --> 13:37.947
- So, the guy's two seconds
from freedom,

13:37.991 --> 13:39.688
and he shoots
a security guard?

13:39.731 --> 13:42.822
So now it's gone from
armed robbery to murder one?

13:42.865 --> 13:44.606
That's the chair,
and he knows it.

13:44.649 --> 13:47.478
- We brought Jimmy in
at least ten times:

13:47.522 --> 13:51.569
assault, bar fights,
even hitting his wife.

13:51.613 --> 13:54.007
He was an angry guy, Bob Lee.

13:54.050 --> 13:55.878
[ambient music]

13:55.922 --> 13:57.706
- Gunshot, alarm,

13:57.749 --> 14:01.492
Jimmy exits, and his car's
parked right here.

14:01.536 --> 14:03.277
Then he just walks?

14:03.320 --> 14:05.061
- That's what the
witnesses said.

14:05.105 --> 14:06.541
- But why?

14:06.584 --> 14:08.543
Weren't you guys coming in hot?

14:08.586 --> 14:11.328
- Yeah, sirens and lights.

14:11.372 --> 14:14.331
[sirens wailing]

14:14.375 --> 14:17.334
[tense music]

14:17.378 --> 14:20.511
♪

14:20.555 --> 14:22.339
- He stops here?

14:22.383 --> 14:24.864
- Yeah, it used to be
a burger joint.

14:24.907 --> 14:27.431
Waitress called in
after we left,

14:27.475 --> 14:29.346
said Jimmy sat here
and ate a cheeseburger

14:29.390 --> 14:31.261
while we were at the bank.

14:31.305 --> 14:33.176
- So, Jimmy Poole
shoots up a bank,

14:33.220 --> 14:34.874
walks four blocks,
and has a bite to eat

14:34.917 --> 14:36.745
while you guys just fly by?

14:36.788 --> 14:38.529
Not a care in the world?

14:38.573 --> 14:41.532
[sirens wailing]

14:41.576 --> 14:43.447
♪

14:43.491 --> 14:46.711
Where'd he go after the burger?
- No idea.

14:46.755 --> 14:50.193
Waitress said she went to call
the cops, and he was gone.

14:50.237 --> 14:53.805
Maybe he was hoping for
a gunfight with your daddy.

14:53.849 --> 14:56.069
Took off when he saw
he wasn't there.

14:56.112 --> 14:59.072
[desolate music]

14:59.115 --> 15:04.033
♪

15:04.077 --> 15:06.470
- He wasn't looking
for a gunfight.

15:06.514 --> 15:09.125
He was waiting for a ride.

15:09.169 --> 15:11.040
Somebody picked him up.

15:11.084 --> 15:13.129
Means he had help.

15:16.524 --> 15:16.916
.

15:16.959 --> 15:19.092
all: ...through Christ,
our Lord. Amen.

15:20.006 --> 15:22.530
- All right, dig in.

15:22.573 --> 15:24.053
- I'm starving.

15:24.097 --> 15:26.447
- Mm, well, slow down,
so you don't choke.

15:26.490 --> 15:27.796
[laughter]

15:27.839 --> 15:29.363
- We worked up
quite an appetite.

15:29.406 --> 15:31.669
- Oh, you did? What did you
and Aunt Anne do today?

15:31.713 --> 15:34.846
- We decided to paint my room.

15:34.890 --> 15:36.718
- Really?
Oh, okay. [laughs]

15:36.761 --> 15:38.676
What color are you gonna
paint your room?

15:38.720 --> 15:40.896
- Daddy's favorite.

15:40.940 --> 15:42.724
- Really, Bob Lee?

15:42.767 --> 15:44.378
- Yep?

15:46.032 --> 15:48.512
You and Aunt Anne
did some painting?

15:48.556 --> 15:49.731
- Close.

15:49.774 --> 15:51.167
- No, we just--
we just prepped it.

15:51.211 --> 15:52.603
We're gonna buy the paint
tomorrow after school.

15:52.647 --> 15:53.953
- Don't worry about,
I'll get it.

15:53.996 --> 15:56.912
- Yeah?
What color?

15:59.959 --> 16:02.048
- Blue.
- [chuckles]

16:02.091 --> 16:05.747
- Good job.
- You got lucky.

16:05.790 --> 16:07.662
[country music playing]

16:07.705 --> 16:10.012
I'm really happy
my sister's here.

16:10.056 --> 16:12.580
It's good for Mary
to have some stability.

16:12.623 --> 16:15.626
- Well, she seems like she's
doing okay with the divorce.

16:15.670 --> 16:17.019
- [chuckles] Hell yeah.

16:17.063 --> 16:18.803
It's the best thing
that ever happened to her.

16:18.847 --> 16:20.762
Her ex was a dick.
You know that.

16:20.805 --> 16:22.416
- Mm.

16:22.459 --> 16:26.202
- By the way,
if you ever try to divorce me,

16:26.246 --> 16:27.638
you should know
I've learned a few things

16:27.682 --> 16:29.118
about shooting
in the last year.

16:29.162 --> 16:31.207
- [chuckles]
You think you could take me?

16:31.251 --> 16:34.515
- Mm, in your current
condition, hell yeah.

16:34.558 --> 16:35.777
Plus, you're never gonna heal

16:35.820 --> 16:38.171
if you don't stay off
your feet, mister.

16:38.214 --> 16:40.129
- I had Sheriff Brown
walk me through the bank

16:40.173 --> 16:42.131
after I stopped by
the work house.

16:42.175 --> 16:44.612
Jimmy Poole
definitely had help.

16:44.655 --> 16:46.527
It could all be connected.

16:46.570 --> 16:49.138
♪

16:49.182 --> 16:51.140
- Look, it was
a long time ago, baby.

16:51.184 --> 16:54.100
You don't feel like
you're chasing ghosts?

16:54.143 --> 16:56.493
- [grunts]
I don't know what I'm chasing,

16:56.537 --> 16:59.757
but you know me, I'm not
really good at sitting still.

16:59.801 --> 17:01.542
- [chuckles]
You're a sniper.

17:01.585 --> 17:03.065
That's your entire job.

17:03.109 --> 17:06.068
- Retired.
- [laughs] Come on.

17:06.112 --> 17:09.332
- I don't know,
I just got this instinct.

17:09.376 --> 17:12.944
I hope I'm wrong, but it's not
gonna go away by ignoring it.

17:12.988 --> 17:15.382
- [exhales]

17:15.425 --> 17:18.776
Baby, I've had enough
adventure for a lifetime.

17:18.820 --> 17:20.517
- You sure?
- [laughs] Yes.

17:20.561 --> 17:22.780
- Huh? Positive?
- No.

17:22.824 --> 17:24.608
♪

17:24.652 --> 17:26.306
- You're gonna be fine.

17:26.349 --> 17:28.047
They'll buy your confidence.
Just do your job.

17:28.090 --> 17:29.831
- This isn't really
my line of work, you know.

17:29.874 --> 17:31.615
- Well, look at it this way,

17:31.659 --> 17:33.574
you don't have a choice.

17:33.617 --> 17:35.358
- Not helping.

17:39.145 --> 17:40.102
Hi.

17:40.146 --> 17:41.277
- Oh, I didn't know
you were back.

17:41.321 --> 17:43.018
You didn't answer
any of my emails.

17:43.062 --> 17:44.759
- Yeah, just grieving,
you know?

17:44.802 --> 17:47.892
- So sad. It's awful.
- Mm, yes...

17:47.936 --> 17:49.503
Yes, but, you know,
back to work, right?

17:49.546 --> 17:51.505
Government's still open, right?
- Yeah, that's true.

17:51.548 --> 17:53.289
- Uh, do you mind?
- Nope, not at all.

17:53.333 --> 17:55.335
- Okay, just a few things
I gotta get for the archive.

17:55.378 --> 17:57.554
- Yeah.
- [softly] Yeah, okay.

18:00.905 --> 18:03.865
[suspenseful music]

18:03.908 --> 18:11.133
♪

18:22.797 --> 18:25.669
- Sir, please step away
from the desk.

18:25.713 --> 18:27.541
- Hi, uh...

18:27.584 --> 18:30.500
I'm Harris Downey.
I--I--I work for Senator Hayes.

18:30.544 --> 18:32.720
- You have an ID?

18:32.763 --> 18:33.938
- Of course.

18:33.982 --> 18:37.855
[tense music]

18:37.899 --> 18:39.335
- Come with me, sir.
- Why?

18:39.379 --> 18:41.076
- Senator Hayes
fired you a week ago.

18:41.120 --> 18:43.034
Your presence here is a felony.

18:43.078 --> 18:45.689
Collect the contents of
the safe and call the FBI.

18:45.733 --> 18:48.039
- Uh...this is a huge mistake.

18:48.083 --> 18:50.346
If--if I could just
actually make a call, uh...

18:50.390 --> 18:53.044
- You have the right
to remain silent. Use it.

18:53.088 --> 18:55.830
♪

18:55.873 --> 18:57.527
- [grunts]

18:57.571 --> 18:59.573
♪

18:59.616 --> 19:02.880
[dog barking]

19:02.924 --> 19:05.187
- Stop it!
Stop it!

19:05.231 --> 19:07.058
[dog barking]

19:07.102 --> 19:09.148
He's not doing anything!
[firecracker pops]

19:09.191 --> 19:10.845
- Oh!
That was crazy!

19:10.888 --> 19:12.890
- This dumb dog.
Oh!

19:12.934 --> 19:14.718
- Better throw it!
Better throw it!

19:14.762 --> 19:16.198
- Oh!

19:16.242 --> 19:18.157
- Stop, you're hurting him.

19:18.200 --> 19:19.549
[firecracker pops]
boys: Whoa!

19:19.593 --> 19:21.986
- Stop!

19:22.030 --> 19:25.555
- That's the point.

19:25.599 --> 19:28.210
- Yeah.

19:28.254 --> 19:30.604
[firecracker pops]
- Little mutt!

19:30.647 --> 19:32.519
[firecrackers popping]

19:32.562 --> 19:34.085
- That's far enough!

19:34.129 --> 19:36.175
- Hey, take it easy.

19:36.218 --> 19:38.046
I ain't here for
a gunfight, Johnny.

19:38.089 --> 19:40.744
- Swaggers ain't good
for much else.

19:40.788 --> 19:42.485
- Yeah, well, I got
a couple questions,

19:42.529 --> 19:44.487
and if you're willing,
I'd like to ask 'em.

19:44.531 --> 19:48.187
- [inhales]
Questions about what?

19:48.230 --> 19:51.407
- About your Uncle Jimmy.

19:51.451 --> 19:54.367
- Holy shit.

19:54.410 --> 19:58.588
Hey, Grandma, get on out here.

19:58.632 --> 20:01.461
This is gonna be fun.

20:01.504 --> 20:03.245
Say hello...

20:03.289 --> 20:06.683
to Bob Lee Swagger.

20:06.727 --> 20:08.685
- Don't look like much.

20:08.729 --> 20:11.862
- You want I should...

20:11.906 --> 20:13.516
send him on his way?

20:13.560 --> 20:16.258
- Let him say his piece.

20:16.302 --> 20:19.479
You here to apologize
for your daddy?

20:19.522 --> 20:22.264
- As far as I can tell,
it was a fair fight.

20:22.308 --> 20:24.092
Losers on both sides.

20:24.135 --> 20:27.051
- Yeah, except your daddy
shot my son in the face.

20:27.095 --> 20:28.444
Couldn't lay him out proper.

20:28.488 --> 20:30.054
- All right, ma'am,
I'm not--I'm not looking

20:30.098 --> 20:32.143
to dig up any unpleasant
memories.

20:32.187 --> 20:33.884
I just had a couple questions.
- So ask.

20:33.928 --> 20:35.973
I got food on the stove.
- All right.

20:36.017 --> 20:39.760
So Jimmy only had two weeks
left at the work farm.

20:39.803 --> 20:41.022
Why'd he run?

20:41.065 --> 20:42.589
- Now we ain't ever
gonna know that.

20:42.632 --> 20:45.418
He had a good job lined up
at the slaughter house.

20:45.461 --> 20:47.507
Would've been set up real nice.

20:47.550 --> 20:49.030
- Bama Cattle?

20:49.073 --> 20:51.815
- Red Bama's done a lot
for this family.

20:51.859 --> 20:53.948
He felt about Jimmy...

20:53.991 --> 20:55.906
and his bitch wife.

20:55.950 --> 20:57.647
♪

20:57.691 --> 20:58.909
- We done here?

20:58.953 --> 20:59.997
- What ever happened
to his wife?

21:00.041 --> 21:01.303
- She skipped.

21:01.347 --> 21:04.088
She couldn't get away
fast enough.

21:04.132 --> 21:07.004
Jimmy was too good
for her, anyway.

21:07.048 --> 21:08.354
- Where'd she go?

21:08.397 --> 21:10.617
- To hell with her...

21:10.660 --> 21:13.576
and to hell with you too.

21:13.620 --> 21:15.143
[gun clicks]

21:15.186 --> 21:16.753
- Time to leave, Swagger.

21:16.797 --> 21:20.453
♪

21:20.496 --> 21:22.977
- Appreciate the time, Johnny.

21:23.020 --> 21:24.935
[dog barking]

21:24.979 --> 21:26.546
- Your dog looks like
you, Suzy.

21:26.589 --> 21:28.722
- Yeah.
[firecracker pops]

21:31.159 --> 21:33.204
[gunshot]

21:33.248 --> 21:35.424
[dog whimpers]

21:46.087 --> 21:48.611
- Hey! Hey...

21:50.265 --> 21:52.223
They ain't telling the truth
about my Aunt Edie.

21:52.267 --> 21:54.138
She's a good person.

21:54.182 --> 21:55.488
- I'm sure she is.

21:55.531 --> 21:58.752
- Sends me a birthday card
every year: $10.

21:58.795 --> 22:01.189
- That's real generous.

22:01.232 --> 22:03.278
You Johnny's kid?

22:03.322 --> 22:06.499
♪

22:06.542 --> 22:09.153
Does your dad have
a lot of friends around or...

22:09.197 --> 22:11.547
- There's always people
around here.

22:11.591 --> 22:13.723
♪

22:13.767 --> 22:15.769
Thanks for saving my dog.

22:15.812 --> 22:22.732
♪

22:28.042 --> 22:30.131
- Do I get a phone call?

22:33.308 --> 22:35.615
[door buzzes]

22:35.658 --> 22:37.747
Oh, thank God.

22:37.791 --> 22:42.143
- Any trouble, Bill?
- None. Easy day.

22:42.186 --> 22:45.755
- Thank you for your help.
I owe you.

22:45.799 --> 22:47.104
- What the hell's going on?

22:47.148 --> 22:49.498
- We needed the contents
of the safe,

22:49.542 --> 22:50.978
and we needed to get it
out of his office

22:51.021 --> 22:53.546
without Atlas knowing.
- So you had me arrested?

22:53.589 --> 22:56.462
- Oh, not really.
Bill's off duty.

22:56.505 --> 22:58.115
There'll be no record.

22:58.159 --> 23:00.596
- But this is--
this is all on purpose?

23:00.640 --> 23:02.424
- It's hard to tell
what's what.

23:02.468 --> 23:04.948
- Well, it's not like
it's gonna be stamped "Atlas."

23:04.992 --> 23:07.124
- Is anybody gonna answer me?

23:07.168 --> 23:09.823
- Thank you for your service.

23:12.913 --> 23:14.567
- You coming?

23:14.610 --> 23:17.004
- Yes.

23:17.047 --> 23:20.007
[tense music]

23:20.050 --> 23:27.318
♪

23:29.930 --> 23:31.671
- Are you with the police?

23:31.714 --> 23:35.675
♪

23:35.718 --> 23:36.763
- Uh, FBI.

23:36.806 --> 23:39.635
- I gave a statement
to Capitol Police.

23:39.679 --> 23:41.028
- I read it.

23:41.071 --> 23:43.422
Beckett, right?

23:43.465 --> 23:45.032
Anything new since you gave
your statement?

23:45.075 --> 23:48.775
- No, the police took Harris
and the contents of the safe.

23:48.818 --> 23:51.125
I didn't even know
we had a safe in here.

23:51.168 --> 23:52.648
- [chuckles]

23:52.692 --> 23:56.565
♪

23:56.609 --> 23:58.611
Do me a favor and call my cell

23:58.654 --> 24:00.656
if you hear from
Mr. Downey again.

24:00.700 --> 24:04.660
♪

24:04.704 --> 24:07.881
[hard rock music playing]

24:07.924 --> 24:14.975
♪

24:21.764 --> 24:23.244
[gunshots]

24:23.287 --> 24:25.551
- [shouting in Spanish]

24:25.594 --> 24:29.076
- I'll give you what you want.
Don't wave that gun in my face.

24:29.119 --> 24:31.165
[tense music]

24:31.208 --> 24:33.341
- [shouting in Spanish]

24:33.384 --> 24:35.386
- I just gotta open--
I just--

24:35.430 --> 24:39.826
- [shouting in Spanish]

24:39.869 --> 24:42.132
♪

24:42.176 --> 24:44.352
- Just open the register.
Please.

24:44.395 --> 24:47.703
- [shouting in Spanish]
- Just get the gun out--

24:47.747 --> 24:49.052
All right!

24:49.096 --> 24:51.011
♪

24:51.054 --> 24:55.058
What do you want?
- [shouting in Spanish]

24:55.102 --> 24:56.712
[groaning]

24:56.756 --> 25:02.544
♪

25:02.588 --> 25:04.894
- Why were you waiting
there for me?

25:04.938 --> 25:07.680
[speaking Spanish]

25:07.723 --> 25:09.508
[fire extinguisher hissing]

25:09.551 --> 25:11.684
[music swells]

25:14.817 --> 25:15.035
.

25:15.078 --> 25:16.645
[siren blaring]

25:16.689 --> 25:17.777
- So, just a regular
fill-up, huh?

25:17.820 --> 25:19.082
- I saw him about a mile back,

25:19.126 --> 25:20.823
and I didn't think
anything of it.

25:20.867 --> 25:22.825
They were following me.
- Yeah? Why?

25:22.869 --> 25:24.348
- Hell if I know.

25:24.392 --> 25:26.220
They both got dried blood
on their clothes.

25:26.263 --> 25:28.875
- That's 'cause they both work
for Bama Cattle.

25:30.441 --> 25:33.096
- I stopped by the Poole farm.

25:33.140 --> 25:34.576
- Damn it, Bob Lee,
what'd you go and do that for?

25:34.620 --> 25:37.144
- Hey, Jimmy Poole said
Johnny had an offer from Bama

25:37.187 --> 25:39.146
to work there after prison.
- So?

25:39.189 --> 25:40.843
- So you don't think it's odd

25:40.887 --> 25:43.672
I start poking around in
Jimmy's memory and now this?

25:43.716 --> 25:46.283
This was an ambush, Sheriff.
The first guy was a decoy,

25:46.327 --> 25:48.590
and second guy was set up
in there, waiting for me,

25:48.634 --> 25:49.983
and I wanna talk to him.

25:50.026 --> 25:52.463
- This was a robbery, Bob Lee,

25:52.507 --> 25:55.728
and any other sane person
would have called 911.

25:55.771 --> 25:58.382
[sighs] Look...

25:58.426 --> 26:01.081
I don't know what's got
your head spinning on Earl,

26:01.124 --> 26:04.824
but there's nothing there.

26:09.393 --> 26:12.005
- Hey, guys,
I'm sorry I'm late.

26:18.098 --> 26:19.708
All right, I'm gonna
jump in the shower,

26:19.752 --> 26:22.711
and then we can eat.

26:22.755 --> 26:25.714
- Come on, it's your turn.

26:25.758 --> 26:27.411
- [sighs]

26:27.455 --> 26:30.414
[somber music]

26:30.458 --> 26:35.898
♪

26:35.942 --> 26:37.247
[door slams]

26:38.684 --> 26:41.251
- It's all coded.

26:41.295 --> 26:43.558
- Well, what'd you expect,
a treasure map?

26:43.602 --> 26:44.907
- Does anybody else care about

26:44.951 --> 26:47.301
the several felonies
we're committing?

26:47.344 --> 26:48.781
- The only one that matters
is treason,

26:48.824 --> 26:51.044
punishable by death.

26:51.087 --> 26:52.567
- That supposed to be funny?

26:52.611 --> 26:55.091
- I recognize some of these
numbers from that ledger.

26:55.135 --> 26:57.267
- Oh, let me see that.

26:57.311 --> 26:59.095
Hm.

26:59.139 --> 27:01.794
Looks like they use
revolving accounts.

27:01.837 --> 27:04.144
- This is something,

27:04.187 --> 27:06.189
and it's not even coded.
- What?

27:06.233 --> 27:07.756
- Names.

27:07.800 --> 27:09.453
Our names.

27:09.497 --> 27:10.933
- [chuckles]

27:10.977 --> 27:13.762
Harris, you made the cut.

27:13.806 --> 27:15.546
- What cut?

27:15.590 --> 27:17.766
[ominous music]

27:17.810 --> 27:19.725
What is this?

27:19.768 --> 27:25.556
♪

27:25.600 --> 27:27.297
- This is a kill list.

27:27.341 --> 27:30.474
- Surprised you're on it?
- Surprised I'm fifth.

27:30.518 --> 27:34.565
- Who's, uh, Carlita Cruise,
Department of Agriculture?

27:34.609 --> 27:35.958
♪

27:36.002 --> 27:37.873
- I don't know.
- Bullshit.

27:37.917 --> 27:41.007
You know everyone.
- I guess not.

27:41.050 --> 27:42.748
- Let's find her.

27:42.791 --> 27:45.794
- [grunting]

27:45.838 --> 27:48.797
[solemn synth music]

27:48.841 --> 27:56.109
♪

27:57.458 --> 27:59.895
They both got dried blood
on their clothes.

27:59.939 --> 28:01.854
- That's 'cause they both work
for Bama Cattle.

28:01.897 --> 28:03.986
- [grunts, exhales]

28:04.030 --> 28:06.815
- Red Bama's done a lot
for this family.

28:06.859 --> 28:08.817
♪

28:08.861 --> 28:10.689
- He was waiting for a ride.

28:10.732 --> 28:12.342
Means he had help.

28:12.386 --> 28:15.345
[panting]

28:15.389 --> 28:16.999
♪

28:17.043 --> 28:19.567
- Bob Lee, come to bed.

28:19.610 --> 28:21.308
♪

28:21.351 --> 28:23.005
- I'm sorry I forgot the paint.

28:23.049 --> 28:26.313
- I'm not the one
that needs the apology.

28:26.356 --> 28:28.010
- Uh, the day just
took a weird turn.

28:28.054 --> 28:29.533
- Oh, I know.

28:29.577 --> 28:31.535
The sheriff called
and told me all about it.

28:31.579 --> 28:33.276
- I didn't go looking for it.

28:33.320 --> 28:36.149
- [chuckles] You never do.

28:36.192 --> 28:38.412
[gentle music]

28:38.455 --> 28:40.675
- What's that supposed to mean?

28:40.719 --> 28:42.459
♪

28:42.503 --> 28:45.027
- You're bleeding. Clean it up
before you come to bed.

28:45.071 --> 28:47.377
♪

28:47.421 --> 28:49.553
[ominous music]

28:49.597 --> 28:51.686
- [exhales sharply]

28:51.730 --> 28:53.383
♪

28:53.427 --> 28:56.560
- Sir? I'm sorry,
you can't go in there.

28:56.604 --> 28:58.040
Sir? Sir?

28:58.084 --> 29:00.477
- What the hell's going on?
- I'm so sorry.

29:00.521 --> 29:02.566
I told him
not to walk in here.

29:02.610 --> 29:04.003
- You Red Bama?

29:04.046 --> 29:06.266
I'm told you're
the man in charge.

29:06.309 --> 29:08.311
I'm Bob Lee Swagger.
- Oh, we're not hiring.

29:08.355 --> 29:11.097
- Actually I heard you might
have two new openings.

29:11.140 --> 29:13.534
- Yeah, well, you heard wrong.

29:13.577 --> 29:15.754
Jane, call Security.

29:15.797 --> 29:17.538
What is it that you want?

29:17.581 --> 29:21.672
- I wanna know why this company
offered Jimmy Poole a job.

29:21.716 --> 29:23.109
- Who's Jimmy Poole?

29:23.152 --> 29:25.154
- He killed my dad...

29:25.198 --> 29:26.765
but you knew that,

29:26.808 --> 29:28.636
or else why would
you send two amateurs

29:28.679 --> 29:30.464
to kill me at a gas station?

29:30.507 --> 29:32.422
You guys still hiring
illegals to cut meat?

29:32.466 --> 29:34.511
- I--I don't know what the hell
you're talking about.

29:34.555 --> 29:37.776
Uh...two illegals
tried to kill you,

29:37.819 --> 29:39.386
and you're here?

29:39.429 --> 29:41.910
Uh, what'd they--they give you
my name or something?

29:41.954 --> 29:43.825
- No.

29:43.869 --> 29:45.435
ICE scooped them up

29:45.479 --> 29:47.350
before they could even
finish being processed.

29:47.394 --> 29:50.484
Never seen the feds
move that fast.

29:50.527 --> 29:53.226
It was almost like
somebody called in a favor.

29:53.269 --> 29:56.533
- Yeah, well, I don't know you
or any Jimmy Poole.

29:56.577 --> 29:58.797
So why don't you get
the hell out of my office?

29:58.840 --> 30:00.450
- Hey, is that you?

30:00.494 --> 30:02.104
- Yes.

30:02.148 --> 30:04.106
- What kinda rifle?

30:04.150 --> 30:05.760
- I don't know.
They're provided.

30:05.804 --> 30:07.414
- Oh.

30:07.457 --> 30:10.765
Well then,
who cut the tail off?

30:10.809 --> 30:12.723
There's no blood on that knife.

30:12.767 --> 30:16.902
[chuckles] Shit,
they shoot it for you too?

30:16.945 --> 30:18.947
Or maybe this guy did.

30:18.991 --> 30:21.950
He looks like a pipe hitter.

30:21.994 --> 30:25.214
- There a reason
why you're here?

30:25.258 --> 30:27.651
- When I hunt,

30:27.695 --> 30:30.872
I like to look at
my prey up close,

30:30.916 --> 30:32.265
see what I'm dealing with.

30:32.308 --> 30:33.962
[brooding music]

30:34.006 --> 30:37.226
You can learn a lot about
an animal when you surprise it,

30:37.270 --> 30:39.011
like where it's weak.

30:39.054 --> 30:46.322
♪

30:57.899 --> 30:58.073
.

30:58.117 --> 31:00.815
- It's pretty boring.
- Nothing wrong with boring.

31:00.859 --> 31:02.208
- Yeah, well,
if Carlita Cruise is here,

31:02.251 --> 31:04.819
she's definitely
not expecting us.

31:04.863 --> 31:06.429
- Or she is.

31:06.473 --> 31:09.432
- Uh, if you guys don't mind,
I'll just sit this one out.

31:09.476 --> 31:11.870
- That's fine by me.

31:11.913 --> 31:14.437
- If we're not back in ten
minutes, you're on your own.

31:16.048 --> 31:17.527
- Love you too, honey.

31:17.571 --> 31:19.355
[knocking on door]

31:19.399 --> 31:21.618
[dog barking distantly]

31:24.491 --> 31:26.275
- Door's unlocked.

31:26.319 --> 31:29.278
[suspenseful music]

31:29.322 --> 31:36.155
♪

31:36.198 --> 31:37.939
- No one's home.

31:37.983 --> 31:40.333
♪

31:40.376 --> 31:42.901
- Wonder if anyone
ever was home.

31:42.944 --> 31:49.472
♪

31:49.516 --> 31:52.475
[cabinet doors closing]

31:52.519 --> 31:54.521
♪

31:54.564 --> 31:56.827
Oh, found something.

31:56.871 --> 31:58.612
[exhales]

31:58.655 --> 32:05.924
♪

32:14.280 --> 32:15.585
Passports.

32:15.629 --> 32:17.936
♪

32:17.979 --> 32:20.112
Huh.

32:20.155 --> 32:21.635
She was prepared.

32:21.678 --> 32:25.682
♪

32:25.726 --> 32:26.945
- Hold on, Nadine!
[explosion]

32:26.988 --> 32:29.208
- Oh!
[high-pitched ringing]

32:31.862 --> 32:35.170
[voices modulated, muffled]

32:38.957 --> 32:41.611
- We should go to the hospital.
- She's fine.

32:41.655 --> 32:43.265
- She could have a concussion.

32:43.309 --> 32:44.658
She could maybe
have a CTE even.

32:44.701 --> 32:46.703
- She's not a professional
football player.

32:46.747 --> 32:49.228
- Yeah--please, I am fine.

32:49.271 --> 32:51.273
[groans] Headache.

32:51.317 --> 32:54.102
- Flash bang in the go-bag.
You're lucky.

32:54.146 --> 32:55.930
That sink saved your life.

32:55.974 --> 32:57.584
- Why would somebody
who works for

32:57.627 --> 32:58.846
the Department of Agriculture
have a go-bag?

32:58.889 --> 33:01.414
- 'Cause she works for Atlas.

33:01.457 --> 33:03.111
She was on the list.
They're cleaning up.

33:03.155 --> 33:06.810
- She's in the wind now
for sure.

33:06.854 --> 33:08.247
- Okay, so, that's it, right?

33:08.290 --> 33:11.032
We're go--we're going
to the police, right?

33:11.076 --> 33:13.382
- We're not going
to the police, Harris.

33:13.426 --> 33:14.993
- Then where, okay?

33:15.036 --> 33:16.690
Uh, you guys are obviously good
at this James Bond shit.

33:16.733 --> 33:18.822
I'm not.
- Okay, look...

33:18.866 --> 33:22.000
I know someone
who can keep you safe.

33:23.697 --> 33:25.786
- Told you not to go
to Bama Cattle.

33:25.829 --> 33:27.092
- But I was right.

33:27.135 --> 33:29.007
Red Junior practically
shit himself.

33:29.050 --> 33:31.487
- He also filed
a restraining order.

33:31.531 --> 33:33.011
He said that
you intimidated him.

33:33.054 --> 33:34.621
He has a witness.
- Oh, come on, that's not true.

33:34.664 --> 33:37.450
I just asked him
a few questions.

33:37.493 --> 33:39.669
- This needs to end, Bob Lee.

33:39.713 --> 33:42.107
- As soon as I know the truth.

33:45.675 --> 33:47.199
- All right.

33:47.242 --> 33:49.201
Take a ride with me.

34:01.561 --> 34:03.041
- This was a long way to go

34:03.084 --> 34:06.000
if you're just trying
to scare me straight.

34:06.044 --> 34:07.306
- Take a seat.

34:17.229 --> 34:18.839
- You remember
what I said to you

34:18.882 --> 34:21.276
the night we found you
in your daddy's cruiser?

34:22.669 --> 34:24.714
- You told me
to forget everything.

34:24.758 --> 34:27.108
- Couldn't imagine
what you must be feeling,

34:27.152 --> 34:29.719
being there
when your daddy died.

34:29.763 --> 34:33.288
Forgetting was
the best I could do.

34:35.421 --> 34:37.771
Radio was on.

34:37.814 --> 34:40.252
I saved the audio.

34:40.295 --> 34:43.255
[mysterious music]

34:43.298 --> 34:45.518
♪

34:45.561 --> 34:48.564
Jimmy Poole killed
your daddy, Bob Lee.

34:48.608 --> 34:50.305
♪

34:50.349 --> 34:51.611
There's no conspiracy.

34:51.654 --> 34:54.179
♪

34:54.222 --> 34:56.572
- Get your ass
out here, Jimmy!

34:56.616 --> 35:00.446
This could all end
without any more bloodshed.

35:00.489 --> 35:02.622
It's all right now.

35:02.665 --> 35:05.059
Ain't nobody else
out here but me.

35:05.103 --> 35:08.106
- Is that you, Swagger?
- Stop right there, Jimmy.

35:08.149 --> 35:11.196
No need to rush things.
Let me see your hands.

35:11.239 --> 35:13.633
- I ain't going back
to that work house!

35:13.676 --> 35:16.723
- You're the one who reached
out to me, remember?

35:16.766 --> 35:19.552
Put your hands up
above your head.

35:19.595 --> 35:22.120
Jimmy?

35:22.163 --> 35:24.165
Damn it, don't!
[gunshots]

35:24.209 --> 35:25.732
- Ahh!

35:25.775 --> 35:27.299
- Jimmy?

35:27.342 --> 35:29.605
I don't wanna
have to kill you.

35:29.649 --> 35:31.390
♪

35:31.433 --> 35:34.436
[gunshots]

35:34.480 --> 35:36.612
Stupid son of a bitch.

35:36.656 --> 35:38.266
♪

35:38.310 --> 35:41.269
[groans]
Shots fired.

35:41.313 --> 35:43.402
This is Sheriff Swagger.

35:43.445 --> 35:46.361
I'm at the windmill
off Route 39.

35:46.405 --> 35:48.494
Suspect is down,
but I've been hit--

35:48.537 --> 35:50.409
[groans]--twice.

35:50.452 --> 35:54.108
Requesting immediate
medical assista--

35:54.152 --> 35:55.979
[body thuds]
[gunshot]

35:56.023 --> 35:58.721
- Say again location, over.

35:58.765 --> 36:00.810
Sheriff, can you hear me?

36:00.854 --> 36:02.899
Sheriff Swagger?

36:04.727 --> 36:07.077
- Sorry to have to
do that to you.

36:07.121 --> 36:09.123
- Play it again, the last part.

36:09.167 --> 36:11.473
- What?
- Just the last few seconds.

36:11.517 --> 36:14.433
[dark ambient music]

36:14.476 --> 36:16.086
[tape rewinds]

36:16.130 --> 36:19.612
- Requesting immediate
medical assista--

36:19.655 --> 36:21.614
[body thuds]
[gunshot]

36:21.657 --> 36:24.399
- Say again location, over.

36:24.443 --> 36:25.661
Sheriff, can you hear me?

36:25.705 --> 36:27.315
[tape rewinds]

36:27.359 --> 36:29.665
- ...immediate
medical assista--

36:29.709 --> 36:32.233
[body thuds]
[gunshot]

36:32.277 --> 36:34.409
- That was a different gun.
- Oh, Jesus, Bob Lee--

36:34.453 --> 36:36.846
- No, no, listen, listen.

36:36.890 --> 36:38.848
[tape rewinding]

36:38.892 --> 36:41.851
[body thuds]
[gunshot]

36:41.895 --> 36:44.724
The report comes
almost a full second late.

36:44.767 --> 36:46.639
Jimmy Poole and my dad
were 20 feet apart.

36:46.682 --> 36:48.728
They would've come together.

36:48.771 --> 36:51.861
[tense music]

36:51.905 --> 36:53.820
- Just what are you saying?

36:53.863 --> 36:57.345
- I'm saying that
Jimmy Poole didn't kill my dad.

36:57.389 --> 36:58.868
There was a second shooter.

36:58.912 --> 37:00.218
[music intensifies]

37:02.829 --> 37:03.221
.

37:03.264 --> 37:04.787
- Absolutely not.

37:04.831 --> 37:06.267
- It's the only way
to know for sure.

37:06.311 --> 37:08.269
- Even if your daddy was
killed by somebody else,

37:08.313 --> 37:10.402
probably a Poole, by the way,

37:10.445 --> 37:12.969
what the hell would
that matter now?

37:13.013 --> 37:16.234
- So, you're okay with my dad's
murderer just walking around?

37:16.277 --> 37:17.757
- Watch your tone, son.

37:17.800 --> 37:19.802
- I heard it too, Sam.

37:19.846 --> 37:21.674
Bob Lee's right.

37:21.717 --> 37:23.415
[gentle music]

37:23.458 --> 37:26.418
- You on board?
- 100%.

37:26.461 --> 37:28.420
The sooner we get this
behind us, the better.

37:28.463 --> 37:31.161
- There was no autopsy,
since it was open and shut.

37:31.205 --> 37:33.338
That means the lead
might still be in there.

37:33.381 --> 37:35.296
♪

37:35.340 --> 37:38.125
- It's a good thing
your daddy is dead.

37:38.168 --> 37:40.301
He'd kill me for doing this.

37:40.345 --> 37:47.308
♪

37:47.352 --> 37:49.658
Last chance.

37:49.702 --> 37:52.270
- I'm ready.
Let's do it.

37:52.313 --> 37:54.620
- He was a stubborn
son of a bitch.

37:54.663 --> 37:56.970
- [chuckles]

37:57.013 --> 37:59.364
- But I won the last fight.

37:59.407 --> 38:02.497
He didn't want any mention
of that Medal of Honor.

38:02.541 --> 38:04.543
- He barely mentioned it
when he was alive.

38:04.586 --> 38:08.329
- Yeah, well,
humility's for the living.

38:08.373 --> 38:11.811
He won it, and I figured
people should know.

38:11.854 --> 38:15.118
- You and Julie wanna
wait back at the station?

38:15.162 --> 38:16.946
- No, we'll wait here.

38:18.905 --> 38:20.776
[tense music]

38:20.820 --> 38:24.084
[engine starts]

38:24.127 --> 38:31.352
♪

38:40.230 --> 38:41.884
- Stop, stop.

38:41.928 --> 38:44.147
- What, are you having
second thoughts?

38:44.191 --> 38:45.671
- This isn't his grave.

38:45.714 --> 38:49.239
- That's his name
right there, son.

38:49.283 --> 38:50.806
It's--it's his.

38:50.850 --> 38:52.460
- No, Dad wanted to be
buried next to vets.

38:52.504 --> 38:55.507
I remember it.
It mattered to him.

38:55.550 --> 38:56.943
These ain't vets.

38:56.986 --> 38:59.075
- Look, maybe the cemetery
moved him.

38:59.119 --> 39:00.816
- I don't think they moved him.

39:00.860 --> 39:03.036
I think someone moved
his headstone.

39:03.079 --> 39:10.348
♪

39:24.057 --> 39:26.059
It's here.

39:26.102 --> 39:28.061
Look.

39:28.104 --> 39:29.889
Veterans on either side,

39:29.932 --> 39:31.499
and the family name
in the middle

39:31.543 --> 39:34.197
matches the other stones
back there.

39:34.241 --> 39:35.721
- He's right.

39:35.764 --> 39:37.940
This just keeps
getting weirder.

39:37.984 --> 39:39.333
♪

39:39.377 --> 39:41.030
Over here!

39:41.074 --> 39:44.033
[music swells]

39:44.077 --> 39:49.865
♪

39:52.868 --> 39:55.175
- I need the jet.
- Need it for what?

39:55.218 --> 39:57.003
- I'm not asking, Bert.

39:57.046 --> 40:00.006
Gas it up and have it ready.
The Caribbean.

40:00.049 --> 40:02.269
- It's hurricane season.
- Well, then the Swiss Alps.

40:02.312 --> 40:04.097
Okay, man?
I don't really give a shit.

40:04.140 --> 40:05.490
- Calm down.

40:05.533 --> 40:07.666
- You don't tell me
what to do, all right?

40:07.709 --> 40:09.755
I want the jet,
and I want it now.

40:09.798 --> 40:11.800
- I'd lay off
that marching powder.

40:11.844 --> 40:14.499
- Who the hell do you think--
- Your dad is on the way,

40:14.542 --> 40:16.370
and he left instructions.

40:16.414 --> 40:18.720
He said you are to stay here
at Bama Cattle,

40:18.764 --> 40:21.984
and continue to operate
as if nothing has changed,

40:22.028 --> 40:24.247
because nothing has.

40:24.291 --> 40:25.684
- [chuckles] Swagger knows.

40:25.727 --> 40:27.555
- Swagger doesn't know shit.

40:27.599 --> 40:30.166
Besides, who are
you more afraid of?

40:30.210 --> 40:32.386
♪

40:32.430 --> 40:33.648
- I'll fly commercial.

40:33.692 --> 40:37.522
- As I said,
you are to stay here.

40:37.565 --> 40:39.959
♪

40:45.530 --> 40:47.619
- Take a seat, Bob Lee.

40:47.662 --> 40:49.185
You're making my head hurt.

40:49.229 --> 40:51.318
- I wanna go in there and make
sure they're doing it right.

40:51.361 --> 40:54.495
- [sighs]
The M.E. is a friend of mine.

40:54.539 --> 40:57.455
He didn't even know
why I was calling him in.

40:57.498 --> 41:00.066
Trust me, it's fine.

41:00.109 --> 41:01.546
[dark ambient music]

41:01.589 --> 41:04.897
Besides a sealed body
after 30 years

41:04.940 --> 41:08.901
is not how you wanna
remember your daddy.

41:08.944 --> 41:11.469
[door opens]

41:11.512 --> 41:13.296
- Well, that was a first.
- What'd you find?

41:13.340 --> 41:16.517
- Three bullets, like you said,
and something else too.

41:16.561 --> 41:18.301
Someone left this patch
on the body.

41:18.345 --> 41:20.347
It wasn't stitched onto
the uniform, like the others,

41:20.390 --> 41:22.088
just draped on top.

41:22.131 --> 41:24.003
♪

41:24.046 --> 41:27.223
- What about the bullets?
Did you weigh 'em?

41:27.267 --> 41:29.661
- Two at 125 grains,

41:29.704 --> 41:32.707
and the bigger one at 173.

41:32.751 --> 41:34.666
- And you removed the bigger
one from the chest wound?

41:34.709 --> 41:36.537
- Correct.
- 173?

41:36.581 --> 41:38.191
- 173's a rifle round.

41:38.234 --> 41:40.802
[tense music]

41:40.846 --> 41:43.065
My dad was killed by a sniper.
